    <title>Add text to DIV using JavaScript</title>
    <p> <b>Instructions:</b> Add the URL for each of the models.  Then click "Add GLB" and "Add USDZ" buttons.  Once both links have been added, copy the entire code to an HTML element.
    </p>
    <style>
    	body, input {
        	font: 17px Calibri;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <p>
    	<input type='button' onclick='addglb()' value='Add GLB'>
    </p>
    
    <p>
    	<input type='button' onclick='addusdz()' value='Add USDZ'>
    </p>
    GLB URL:    <input type="text" name="glb" id="glb"><br/>
    USDZ URL:    <input type="text" name="usdz" id="usdz"><br/>

<p> <b>Copy the code below:</b></p>

  	<div id='code1'>
    	<p>
        	&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;
	&lt;title&gt;3D Model AR&lt;/title&gt;
